cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on analyzing human mobility patterns using location-based social media data, specifically Twitter. This falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as well as data mining (cs.SD). The use of demographic information and its impact on mobility patterns suggests a potential fit for the categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the study of urban planning and transportation engineering mentioned in the abstract suggests a possible fit for the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
